<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="grand-adj">grand <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ɡrænd/    美 /ɡrænd/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>雄伟的；壮丽的；盛大的；宏大的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a grand view of sunrise 
日出的壮丽景色</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>London has many grand buildings.
伦敦有许多宏伟的建筑。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the Grand Canyon
大峡谷</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Tianjin Grand Theatre
天津大剧院</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>重大的；主要的；(官衔、地位) 最高的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the grand prize 
大奖</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>the Grand Old Man of</strong> British theatre
英国戏剧泰斗</p></div></div>